    {
      "name": "DSPDTA",
      "description": "Display any file",
      "help": "Display any file (DSPDTA)\n\nSpecifies whether users who have authority to read the output queue can display the data of any spooled file on the queue or only the data in their own files.",
      "inputType": "dropdown",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*NO",
      "attributes": {
        "characterSet": "upper"
      },
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "*NO",
          "value": "*NO"
        },
        {
          "label": "*YES",
          "value": "*YES"
        },
        {
          "label": "*OWNER",
          "value": "*OWNER"
        }
      ],
      "positional": 2
    },
    {
      "name": "JOBSEP",
      "description": "Job separators",
      "help": "Job separators (JOBSEP)\n\nSpecifies, for each job with files on the output queue, the number of separators placed at the beginning of the output for the job. Each separator contains information that identifies the job, such as the name of the job, the job user's name, the job number, and the time and date when the job is run.\n\nThis parameter is used only by printer writers, all other types of writers will ignore the value specified for this parameter.\n\n指定できる特殊値: *MSG",
      "inputType": "text",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "0",
      "attributes": {
        "characterSet": "upper"
      },
      "positional": 3
    },
    {
      "name": "OPRCTL",
      "description": "Operator controlled",
      "help": "Operator controlled (OPRCTL)\n\nSpecifies whether a user who has job control authority is allowed to manage or control the files on this output queue.",
      "inputType": "dropdown",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*YES",
      "attributes": {
        "characterSet": "upper"
      },
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "*YES",
          "value": "*YES"
        },
        {
          "label": "*NO",
          "value": "*NO"
        }
      ],
      "positional": 4
    },
    {
      "name": "DTAQ",
      "description": "Data queue",
      "help": "Data queue (DTAQ)\n\nSpecifies the data queue associated with the output queue. Entries are logged in the data queue when spooled files are in ready (RDY) status on the output queue. A user program can determine when a spooled file is available on an output queue using the Receive Data Queue API (QRCVDTAQ) to receive information from a data queue.\n\nEach time a spooled file on the output queue reaches RDY status, an entry is sent to the data queue. A spooled file can have several changes in status (for example, RDY to held (HLD) to release (RLS) to RDY again) before it is taken off the output queue. These status changes result in entries in the data queue for a spooled file each time the spooled file goes to RDY status.\n\nWhen the data queue is created using the Create Data Queue (CRTDTAQ) command, the maximum message length (MAXLEN parameter) value should be at least 128 and the sequence (SEQ parameter) value should be *FIFO or *LIFO. More information about data queues on output queues is in the Printing category in the IBM i Information Center at http://www.ibm.com/systems/i/infocenter/.\n\nSingle values\n\nQualifier 1: Data queue\n\nQualifier 2: Library",
      "inputType": "group",
      "required": false,
      "groupKind": "qualified",
      "singleValues": [
        "*NONE"
      ],
      "children": [
        {
          "name": "DTAQ_LIB",
          "description": "Library",
          "help": "指定できる特殊値: *LIBL, *CURLIB",
          "inputType": "text",
          "required": false,
          "defaultValue": "*LIBL",
          "attributes": {
            "characterSet": "upper",
            "maxLength": 10
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "DTAQ",
          "description": "Data queue",
          "inputType": "text",
          "required": false,
          "attributes": {
            "characterSet": "upper",
            "maxLength": 10
          },
          "defaultValue": "*NONE"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "AUTCHK",
      "description": "Authority to check",
      "help": "Authority to check (AUTCHK)\n\nSpecifies what type of authorities to the output queue allow the user to control all the files on the queue. Users with some special authority may also be able to control the spooled files.",
      "inputType": "dropdown",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*OWNER",
      "attributes": {
        "characterSet": "upper"
      },
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "*OWNER",
          "value": "*OWNER"
